title: Stourbridge host Harriers in the FA Cup
text:
FA Cup journey begins with extra prelims 
Elsewhere, minnows Sporting Khalsa, the joint-lowest side left in the competition, face a spectacular tie. 
They could host the might of FC United of Manchester - should they see off tomorrow night's replay at Spalding United. 
Ian Rowe's giant-killing heroes travel to Lincolnshire, after Dave Meese's last minute penalty on Saturday earned them a dramatic replay. 
If they prevail in tomorrow's replay at Stalybridge Celtic, Chasetown have been drawn at home against another National League North side in North Ferriby United. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
Dave Stringer's men drew 1-1 with Celtic at the Scholars Ground on Saturday, James Dance striking early for the Scholars. 
The next phase of the competition - the last before the first round proper - will commence on the weekend beginning October 24. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
